    <title>Linear resolutions and Gr√∂bner basis of Hankel determinantal ideals</title>
    <summary>  In this paper, we study the family of determinantal ideals of "close" cuts of
Hankel matrices, say $ \mathcal{f} $. We show that the multi-Rees algebra of
ideals in $ \mathcal{f} $ is defined by a quadratic Gr\"{o}bner basis, it is
Koszul, normal Cohen-Macaulay domain and it has a nice Sagbi basis. As a
consequence of Koszulness, we prove that every product $ I_1\ldots I_l $ of
ideals of $ \mathcal{f} $ has linear resolution. Moreover, we show that natural
generators of every product $ I_1\ldots I_l $ form a Gr\"{o}bner basis.
</summary>
